♪ Cos I'm so crazy...

02:23.501 --> 02:26.417
The problem with gold
is the effect it has on people.

02:27.876 --> 02:29.959
Drives them crazy.

02:30.834 --> 02:34.584
- I blame the Old Testament.
- (chuckles)

02:34.709 --> 02:36.626
I've been stocktaking.

02:36.751 --> 02:39.542
Rounding up the scraps,
putting them to good use.

02:39.667 --> 02:41.584
I always find gold a bit vulgar.

02:42.251 --> 02:44.209
Silver's more discreet.

02:44.626 --> 02:46.667
Let me tell you something: over the years,

02:46.792 --> 02:49.751
I have made more money out of gold

02:49.876 --> 02:53.001
than all the great train robbers
put together.

02:54.626 --> 02:56.834
I want you to stay out of mischief.

02:57.334 --> 02:59.001
What have you got to prove?

03:02.459 --> 03:05.042
You remember when we used to meet
at the Savoy?

03:05.876 --> 03:07.584
Then we used to have dinner.

03:07.709 --> 03:10.584
- On Jermyn Street at Wiltons.
- (chuckles)

03:10.709 --> 03:12.334
Frederick's.

03:12.459 --> 03:14.376
Le Gavroche. (chuckles)

03:14.751 --> 03:16.501
All that green velvet.

03:16.626 --> 03:18.417
Ooh, I've got an idea.

03:18.542 --> 03:21.251
Why don't you have
a lovely glass of white wine?

03:21.376 --> 03:23.001
Just for old times' sake.

03:24.667 --> 03:26.751
Not for me.

03:27.626 --> 03:29.001
Thank you.

03:29.542 --> 03:33.501
I just want to keep fresh
for the hospital tomorrow.

03:43.001 --> 03:45.084
That crème brûlée at Wiltons.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.709
That was like losing my virginity.

03:47.834 --> 03:48.876
(she chuckles)

03:49.001 --> 03:51.501
I remember you losing your virginity.

03:52.792 --> 03:55.459
- Like V-E Day.
- (he chuckles)

03:59.292 --> 04:01.376
♪ The Touch Of Your Lips

04:01.834 --> 04:03.709
Thank you.

04:07.667 --> 04:08.709
Ooh.

04:08.834 --> 04:10.501
- That's marvellous.
- (chuckles)

04:10.626 --> 04:12.167
Good.

04:19.209 --> 04:20.916
Sorry.

04:21.750 --> 04:23.084
I'll just be a moment.

04:23.209 --> 04:24.334
All right?

04:54.709 --> 04:58.542
(whistles and bangs)

05:03.917 --> 05:05.292
Yeah. Now,

05:05.751 --> 05:07.042
you see, Terry,

05:07.167 --> 05:10.959
that, believe it or not,
is a Roman Candle.

05:13.459 --> 05:18.001
Now, here we've got a load of
what's known as cakes.

05:18.792 --> 05:22.126
This also includes Roman Candles.

05:22.376 --> 05:25.001
Just say "fireworks, assorted, very loud".

05:25.126 --> 05:28.251
- Why complicate it?
- It don't work like that no more, Terry.

05:28.376 --> 05:30.334
Stuff used to fall off
the back of a lorry.

05:30.459 --> 05:33.001
You could sell it on, no questions asked.

05:33.126 --> 05:37.042
Nowadays everybody wants a guarantee.

05:37.584 --> 05:39.084
Sell them on the internet.

05:39.917 --> 05:42.126
Terry, I'm having no truck
with internet shopping.

05:42.251 --> 05:45.876
How the fuck you supposed to fiddle
somebody over the fucking internet?

05:46.001 --> 05:48.417
If you can't hold it in your hand,
it ain't worth nicking.

05:48.542 --> 05:51.209
The trouble is, Terry,
I've got no security.

05:51.334 --> 05:54.209
What have I got to fall back on
when I retire?

05:54.334 --> 05:57.251
I haven't got a proper job like you have,
Terry.

06:01.876 --> 06:03.126
Just do it, Terry!

06:03.251 --> 06:05.417
It's really busy.
I don't have time for this.

06:06.626 --> 06:10.001
We take the matter of outstanding debt
very seriously here.

06:10.126 --> 06:11.167
- So...
- Yes.

06:11.292 --> 06:14.876
I'm afraid if you can't guarantee you
don't have outstanding loans elsewhere

06:15.001 --> 06:18.751
or you can't guarantee that you'll
pay us back, then I can't help.

06:19.084 --> 06:20.542
Well, I can.

06:20.667 --> 06:22.292
I can guarantee it.

06:22.459 --> 06:25.834
What? That you'll pay it back
or you don't have outstanding loans?

06:25.959 --> 06:27.584
Both.

06:27.709 --> 06:29.126
Neither.

06:29.417 --> 06:31.042
Were you in here last week?

06:32.626 --> 06:34.126
No. No.

06:34.251 --> 06:35.626
You look very familiar.

06:35.751 --> 06:37.792
No, I can assure you, you don't know me.

06:37.917 --> 06:41.626
You've already applied for an account and
we've turned you down. I remember you.

06:43.917 --> 06:46.084
You know the trouble with people like you?

06:47.126 --> 06:48.501
Tell me.

06:49.084 --> 06:50.251
You're thieves.

06:50.626 --> 06:52.626
- Really?
- Mm.

06:52.751 --> 06:53.959
I'll show meself out.

06:57.001 --> 06:58.792
Have a nice day.

06:58.917 --> 07:01.542
♪ TOM JONES:
What'cha Gonna Do

