♪ What'cha gonna do?

07:31.667 --> 07:34.626
♪ What'cha gonna do
when your baby leaves you?

07:34.751 --> 07:37.292
- Good luck.
- ♪ What'cha gonna do?

07:40.042 --> 07:44.876
The first job I got arrested for
was a tin of peaches.

07:46.126 --> 07:47.917
- I was 13.
- See?

07:48.042 --> 07:49.709
Always food.

07:49.834 --> 07:50.876
Yeah.

07:51.001 --> 07:54.042
You feel so guilty
when the family finds out.

07:54.167 --> 07:55.709
Nah, your old man was worse.

07:55.834 --> 07:58.001
No, no, but it never goes, does it, Ken?

07:58.126 --> 08:02.959
I mean, you grow up, you have kids,
so you feel guilty all over again.

08:03.334 --> 08:05.792
You paid the bills, Brian.
You looked after everyone.

08:05.917 --> 08:07.292
Yeah, look after yourself now.

08:07.417 --> 08:09.251
Yeah, I gotta find a hobby.

08:09.501 --> 08:11.292
Yeah, find something
you really like doing.

08:11.417 --> 08:12.459
(they chuckle)

08:12.584 --> 08:14.876
- A guilty pleasure.
- Yeah.

08:15.459 --> 08:19.876
I heard a rumour they're closing down
the post office in Great Portland Street.

08:20.292 --> 08:22.209
Lovely big bureau de change.

08:22.334 --> 08:24.417
You wanna nip in there
while they're winding it all up.

08:24.542 --> 08:27.126
- Catch them with their trousers down.
- Not that kind of hobby.

08:27.251 --> 08:29.167
She told me to stay out of trouble.

08:30.459 --> 08:31.959
Thank you...

08:33.751 --> 08:37.208
The Agricultural Bank of China
in Pimlico.

08:37.626 --> 08:39.708
Always fancied a crack at that.

08:40.292 --> 08:43.626
If the Agricultural Bank of China
doesn't do it for you, nothing will.

08:43.751 --> 08:45.584
Or Hatton Garden.

08:45.709 --> 08:47.376
We haven't talked about that for a while.

08:47.501 --> 08:50.792
Too many stairs for me at my age.
I'm retired.

08:50.917 --> 08:53.417
We could always install a stair-lift.

08:53.542 --> 08:54.751
That's a lovely vault, that.

08:54.876 --> 08:58.292
Yeah, there's something terribly
reassuring about a nice vault.

08:58.751 --> 09:00.334
Get some young blokes in.

09:00.917 --> 09:04.334
Danny Jones is still sniffing around
for work. He's only 60.

09:04.459 --> 09:06.584
Yeah, you can rely on Danny.

09:06.709 --> 09:07.876
As straight as they come.

09:08.001 --> 09:10.292
All right, mate.
Mind your back there, governor.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.626
(clears his throat)

09:13.126 --> 09:14.542
- (cries of surprise)
- Whoop!

09:14.917 --> 09:16.084
What's he up to?

09:16.209 --> 09:18.751
Where the fuck does he think he is,
the fucking circus?

09:19.209 --> 09:21.001
I'll have a word with him, calm him down.

09:22.167 --> 09:24.251
Has he no sense of occasion?

09:26.917 --> 09:28.709
Here we go.

09:29.501 --> 09:31.376
All right, Danny boy?

09:31.959 --> 09:33.459
- Hello, Terence.
- Take him home.

09:33.584 --> 09:34.959
Women like Danny.

09:35.084 --> 09:36.501
He's a shagger.

09:36.626 --> 09:38.751
Yeah, I had no truck with shaggers.

09:39.126 --> 09:41.209
They can't keep their mouths shut.

09:44.834 --> 09:46.251
- (woman laughs)
- (Danny laughs)

09:46.751 --> 09:48.667
I'm so sorry, Brian.

09:48.792 --> 09:49.917
Thank you, Basil.

09:50.042 --> 09:53.126
Yeah, I only met her twice
but she left a lasting impression.

09:53.251 --> 09:54.834
She did.

09:54.959 --> 09:56.334
She certainly did.

09:57.709 --> 09:59.792
Security Express, Shoreditch,

09:59.917 --> 10:04.459
the biggest cash robbery
in the history of... cash robberies.

10:04.584 --> 10:05.834
And d'you know how?

10:05.959 --> 10:08.667
We used our brains. Psychological.

10:08.792 --> 10:11.792
Doused them in petrol,
talked to them in Northern Irish accents.

10:11.917 --> 10:14.376
They shit 'emselves
that you was gonna blow 'em up.

10:14.501 --> 10:16.376
Kicked 'em in the biscuits, pointed a gun,

10:16.501 --> 10:18.334
kicked 'em in the cobblers,
up the Aristotle.

10:18.459 --> 10:21.292
- But we never fucking hurt them.
- No, we never.

10:21.417 --> 10:23.792
- Have you finished?
- Yeah.

10:23.917 --> 10:26.959
Stop talking shop.
She'll turn in her grave.

10:27.959 --> 10:30.042
- You're right, Brian.
- Yeah, cheers.

10:30.959 --> 10:32.209
Yeah.

10:45.167 --> 10:46.209
(doorbell)

10:46.334 --> 10:47.917
Fucking hell.

10:53.084 --> 10:54.459
Hi, Brian.

10:55.584 --> 10:57.334
Come in.

11:03.209 --> 11:04.501
Have I caught you at a bad time?

11:04.626 --> 11:06.376
Nah, I'm not doing anything.

11:07.292 --> 11:09.292
Sweet Fanny Adams.

11:12.917 --> 11:14.667
Certainly nice and quiet.

11:14.792 --> 11:16.251
When somebody dies,

11:16.376 --> 11:21.084
nothing prepares you
for the silence of an empty house.

11:29.709 --> 11:34.542
I, I, I can't believe that she's never
ever gonna walk through the door again.

11:36.001 --> 11:37.626
Ever.

11:44.334 --> 11:47.209
- Brian, do you want me to mow the lawn?
- No, the mower's broke.

11:47.584 --> 11:50.126
Oh. Built-in obsolescence.

11:50.751 --> 11:51.959
You want a cup of tea?

11:53.834 --> 11:55.126
Er...

11:55.251 --> 11:57.751
- You got anything to drink?
- No, I'm on the water wagon.

11:57.876 --> 11:59.917
I gave up alcohol when Lyn did.

12:00.917 --> 12:03.709
She, she couldn't even get a strong drink
when she needed it.

12:04.251 --> 12:06.001
Well, what about if you need it?

12:06.209 --> 12:08.209
Well, I do as it happens.

12:08.334 --> 12:10.417
♪ Blues By Five

12:12.292 --> 12:14.709
So, what's going on?

12:15.834 --> 12:18.876
- Oh, this and that.
- This? And that?

12:19.001 --> 12:20.376
At once?

12:20.501 --> 12:21.959
Well, that sounds tiring.

12:22.084 --> 12:23.959
I've been working.

12:24.084 --> 12:26.667
Wiring, you know. Various things.

12:26.792 --> 12:28.751
Working, wiring, various things.

12:28.876 --> 12:32.626
I can hardly stand
the fucking excitement. (laughs)

12:33.501 --> 12:35.001
Yeah, no, I...

12:35.126 --> 12:38.459
I got into fibre optics,
telecommunications.

12:38.751 --> 12:40.834
You haven't gone straight again,
have you?

12:40.959 --> 12:42.792
I quite like working.

12:42.917 --> 12:44.292
Quite good at it.

12:44.417 --> 12:48.459
I nearly went straight once after
the Bond Street job went tits up.

12:49.959 --> 12:51.667
I thought my time had come.

12:51.792 --> 12:53.126
Quit while you were ahead.

12:53.251 --> 12:54.709
I wasn't ahead.

12:54.834 --> 12:56.251
That was the trouble.

12:57.459 --> 12:59.584
If you'd have been in, I might have been.

13:07.126 --> 13:09.042
There was a bit of talk at the funeral.

13:09.167 --> 13:11.292
No, there wasn't.

13:11.417 --> 13:13.126
- Not at that funeral.
- OK.

13:19.751 --> 13:22.626
I haven't been to Hatton Garden
in 25 years, son.

13:23.001 --> 13:24.959
- Not since the glory days.
- (chuckles)

13:27.126 --> 13:29.417
Well, if you don't have a go,
somebody else will.

13:41.126 --> 13:45.709
Turns out I know someone
who knows someone who has a key.

13:46.376 --> 13:47.959
As it happens.

13:48.084 --> 13:50.001
Someone in the business.

13:50.126 --> 13:51.459
Now you tell me.

13:52.626 --> 13:54.292
Yeah, well, I only just thought of it.

13:54.417 --> 13:57.751
Oh, get over it. You've been
wanting to tell me all evening.

13:58.376 --> 14:00.626
That's why you offered to mow my lawn.

14:04.834 --> 14:06.876
Why didn't you say so before?

14:08.376 --> 14:10.001
I'm nervous about it.

14:12.542 --> 14:13.876
So am I.

15:41.876 --> 15:44.167
<i>Tell me about this friend of yours.</i>

15:44.292 --> 15:46.126
<i>The one with the key.</i>

15:46.251 --> 15:47.334
<i>Her husband was in gold.</i>

15:47.459 --> 15:49.792
<i>- He had an office in the building.
- Oh, yeah.</i>

15:49.917 --> 15:52.126
<i>I used to sell him the odd thing
from time to time.</i>

15:52.792 --> 15:54.084
<i>When he died, she asked me</i>

15:54.209 --> 15:57.209
<i>if I could go into the office
and clear it out, you know.</i>

15:57.334 --> 15:59.459
<i>Get rid of anything
that could be connected to her.</i>

15:59.584 --> 16:01.209
<i>She trusted you with the key?</i>

16:01.334 --> 16:04.167
Yeah, she couldn't go in herself,
could she? It's too risky.

16:04.292 --> 16:06.084
Risky?

16:06.209 --> 16:07.959
Yeah, Brian.
There's a lot of crooks about.

16:08.084 --> 16:10.167
Oh, yeah, they're all bent down here.

16:10.459 --> 16:12.001
Part of the mystique.

16:14.251 --> 16:15.501
- (whirring)
<i>- Look, see this?</i>

16:15.626 --> 16:18.167
E, D, F, that's a pure diamond.

16:18.292 --> 16:21.334
It's colourless,
so it lets in the most light.

16:21.959 --> 16:24.334
Up there, X, Y, Z.

16:24.459 --> 16:27.126
You cut that too shallow,
you lose the light out of the bottom.

16:27.251 --> 16:30.459
You cut it too deep,
you lose the light out of the side.

16:31.042 --> 16:34.084
FL, that's a flawless diamond.

16:35.209 --> 16:39.334
A flawless diamond,
cut well, in the right light,

16:40.126 --> 16:42.167
is the strangest thing

16:42.292 --> 16:45.417
and the most beautiful thing
you will ever see.

16:46.542 --> 16:47.792
It's true.

16:48.751 --> 16:50.834
They'll be in the vault
over the weekend.

16:53.584 --> 16:56.042
How much is a flawless
six-carat diamond worth?

16:57.001 --> 16:59.084
A million quid to you.

17:00.084 --> 17:02.084
How many of those are in the vault?

17:02.209 --> 17:03.834
A few.

17:03.959 --> 17:05.584
You only need a few.

17:24.709 --> 17:27.291
One... three, nine.

17:27.791 --> 17:28.876
What's wrong?

17:29.001 --> 17:31.042
I'm just checking for wear on the pads.

17:31.167 --> 17:33.709
You can work out the code
by identifying the most worn ones.

17:33.834 --> 17:35.917
Oh, I see.

17:37.292 --> 17:38.626
No.

17:40.376 --> 17:42.417
Take your own time, son.

17:42.542 --> 17:44.751
It's just a process of elimination.

17:45.167 --> 17:46.417
No kidding.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.501
- (double bleep)
- Yeah.

17:49.626 --> 17:51.042
- Cor blimey.
- (alarm)

17:52.751 --> 17:54.959
Right, that's the 60-second alarm.

17:56.042 --> 17:59.209
There's another in the vault with
a GPS feed to a monitoring system.

17:59.876 --> 18:01.334
Does she know the code?

18:01.459 --> 18:03.001
No, I don't need the code.

18:04.834 --> 18:07.292
It's a 20-year-old wireless, unencrypted.

18:08.084 --> 18:10.626
- You know what that means?
- I don't as it happens.

18:10.959 --> 18:12.501
Unauthenticated signals.

18:20.792 --> 18:22.876
(alarm stops)

18:23.292 --> 18:26.584
You know this lift
won't go down to the basement.

18:26.792 --> 18:28.334
What? It's disabled?

18:28.459 --> 18:29.792
Why would they do that?

18:29.917 --> 18:32.751
Because the ride down
takes you to the airlock,

18:32.876 --> 18:35.001
where you can
open the security gate.

18:38.126 --> 18:40.917
Someone tried it, 20 years ago.

18:41.626 --> 18:46.292
Which is why the security company
stopped it from going down.

18:47.417 --> 18:49.084
But I got a better idea.

18:51.459 --> 18:54.709
If we can stop this lift
on the third floor,

18:55.167 --> 18:58.376
we can go down the shaft
and the vault is ours.

18:58.709 --> 19:01.209
Its a 20-foot drop.

19:03.167 --> 19:04.626
Don't sprain your ankle.

19:04.751 --> 19:06.876
Well, how do we
get through the vault door?

19:07.001 --> 19:09.167
We don't.
We go through a hole in the wall.

19:09.292 --> 19:11.209
We drill as big a hole as possible

19:11.334 --> 19:13.876
and we look for the most
undernourished thief we can find

